# Cursor Rules for FlowBoard AI

## Project Setup
- This is a Next.js 15 project using React 19
- Use TypeScript for all code
- Project uses /src folder structure - use existing folders in /src, don&apos;t recreate them outside
- Use absolute imports with &apos;@&apos; prefix instead of relative paths

## UI Framework & Styling
- **ALWAYS use Shadcn UI for ALL UI elements** - no custom components unless absolutely necessary
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- If Shadcn is not initialized, run: `npx shadcn@latest init --yes`
- To add Shadcn components, use: `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`
- Example: `npx shadcn@latest add button` for button component

## Next.js Best Practices
- Use Next.js Server Components whenever possible
- Use Next.js Server Actions whenever possible
- Leverage built-in Next.js optimizations (Image, Link, etc.)

## Database & Validation
- Use database schema from @/lib/db/schema.ts as SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH
- **NEVER modify or remove anything from database schema unless explicitly requested**
- Generate validation schemas, forms, and actions based on existing database schema

## Code Quality
- Use HTML entities: &apos; for single quotes to fix unescaped entity warnings
- Be accurate and thorough in implementations
- Provide immediate, actionable solutions
- Focus on practical code over explanations unless specifically requested

## File Organization
- Follow existing /src folder structure
- Use absolute imports (@/...) for all internal imports
- Keep components modular and reusable

## Development Workflow
- Install missing Shadcn components as needed during development
- Prioritize Server Components and Server Actions
- Maintain consistency with existing project patterns 